ce]] at Gallipoli and the Western Front during the [[First World War]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/tv/programs/anzac-girls/|title=ANZAC Girls|work=ABC Television|accessdate=5 May 2015}}</ref>  The series is based on Peter Rees' book ''[[The Other ANZACs]]'' as well as diaries, letters, photographs  and historical documents.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.canberra.edu.au/monitor/2014/aug/uc-screenwriter|title=ANZAC unsung heroines honoured by UC screenwriter|work=canberra.edu.au|accessdate=5 May 2015}}</ref>\nThe series was written by Felicity Packard and Niki Aken, produced by Screentime, and filmed in [[South Australia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2014/07/airdate-anzac-girls.html|title=Airdate: ANZAC Girls|work=TV Tonight|accessdate=5 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\nCast members include:<ref>{{cite web|title=ANZAC Girls: Media Kit|url=http://clpr.com.au/pdf/work/ANZAC_Girls_Delivery_Media_Kit_27.11.13.pdf|publisher=Screentime  & [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation]]|accessdate=5 November 2015|date=27 November 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Anna McGahan]] as Sister Olive Haynes\n* [[Caroline Craig]] as [[Grace Wilson|Matron Grace Wilson]]\n* [[Georgia Flood]] as Sister [[Alice Ross-King]]\n* [[Laura Brent]] as Sister Elsie Cook \n* [[Antonia Prebble]] as Sister Hilda Steele\n* [[Todd Lasance]] as Major Sydney \"Syd\" Cook \n* [[Dustin Clare]] as Lieutenant Harry Moffitt\n* [[Brandon McClelland (actor)]] as Lieutenant [[Norval 'Pat' Dooley]]\n* [[John Waters (actor)|John Waters]] as Colonel Thomas Fiaschi\n* [[Charles Mayer (actor)|Charles Mayer]] as Major Xavier Leopold\n* [[Thomas Cocquerel]] as Lieutenant Frank Smith\n* [[Honey Debelle]] as Sister [[Kit McNaughton]]\n* [[Rhondda Findleton]] as Matron Ellen \"Nellie\" Gould\n* [[Sara West]]  as Clarice Daley\n* [[Leon Ford]]  as Major John Prior\n* [[Hannah Marshall (actress)|Hannah Marshall]] as Sister Millicent Parker\n* [[Charlotte Hazzard]] as Sister Florence Tilly\n* [[Madeleine Jevic]] as Sister Meg Hayes\n* [[Nathaniel Dean]] as Major Lionel Quick\n* [[Brad Williams (actor)|Brad Williams]] as Major Archibald Springer\n* [[Nicholas Bell]] as General William Birdwood\n* [[Josef Ber]] as Major Sherwin\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |background=#BFE0BF |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |airdate= |overallT=No. |episodes=\n\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 1\n |Title= Adventure\n |DirectedBy= Ken Cameron\n |WrittenBy= Felicity Packard\n |OriginalAirDate= {{start date|2014|8|10|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=The nurses arrive from Australia to Egypt. Each is prepared for a grand adventure, although some seem to have ideas other than nursing on their minds. However, as the Gallipoli Campaign begins in earnest, all of them must face the harsh reality of war, and of what it means to be an ANZAC Nurse.\n |LineColor=bfe0bf\n }}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 2\n |Title= Duty\n |DirectedBy= Ken Cameron\n |WrittenBy= Niki Aken, Felicity Packard\n |OriginalAirDate={{start date|2014|8|17|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary= Olive and the others begin their work on the Greek Island of Lemnos, caring for the wounded who arrive from the Dardanelles with limited supplies and support from the Australian Army. Elsie fights to be able to provide proper care for Syd in Egypt.\n |LineColor=bfe0bf\n }}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 3\n |Title= Endurance\n |DirectedBy= Ken Cameron\n |WrittenBy= Niki Aken, Felicity Packard\n |OriginalAirDate={{start date|2014|8|24|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary= The situation in Lemnos grows darker, as Olive and the others struggle to continue their work in disheartening circumstances. Elsie is faced with a difficult choice when it comes to her continued care of Syd, and Alice also has a choice to make in matters of the heart.  \n |LineColor=bfe0bf\n }}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 4\n |Title= Love\n |DirectedBy= Ian Watson\n |WrittenBy= Felicity Packard\n |OriginalAirDate={{start date|2014|8|31|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary= After the Gallipoli evacuation, the Lemnos nurses have returned, but all the nurses are then sent to France as fighting on the Western Front intensifies. There is prejudice from the British Imperial Nurses to contend with, the first anniversary of ANZAC Day, and Olive begins to question her relationship with Dooley. Alice receives shocking news from the Front.\n |LineColor=bfe0bf\n }}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 5\n |Title= Mateship\n |DirectedBy= Ian Watson\n |WrittenBy= Niki Aken\n |OriginalAirDate={{start date|2014|9|7|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary= Alice struggles to comprehend the news she receives in the wake of an Allied assault in Fromelles. Olive's work at the clearing station brings matters of death, love, and duty to a head. Hilda and a handful of nurses are given the opportunity to work in anaesthetisation, and the arrival of the Croix Rouge leads to the return of a familiar face as another departs.\n |LineColor=bfe0bf\n }}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 6\n |Title= Courage\n |DirectedBy= Ian Watson\n |WrittenBy= Felicity Packard\n |OriginalAirDate={{start date|2014|9|14|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary= Alice and Hilda start work at a clearing station close to the Front, and Elsie follows Syd to the Front. Tensions run high as the final push begins, and our nurses face new dangers. But finally, the Great War reaches its close as Armistice is declared, and we discover what became of our ANZAC Girls.\n |LineColor=bfe0bf\n }}\n }}\n\n==Ratings==\n{{Australian television episode ratings\n| generic      = 1 | hidetimeslot = 1\n\n| title1      = [[#ep1|Adventure]]\n| date1       = 10 August 2014\n| OVviewers1  = 1,062,000\n| OVrank1     = 5\n| CONviewers1 = 187,000\n| CONrank1    = 2\n| total1      = 1,249,000\n| ref1        = <ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvtonight.com.au/2014/08/sunday-10-august-2014.html|title=Sunday 10 August 2014|publisher=TV Tonight|first=David|last=Knox|date=11 August 2014|accessdate=21 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvtonight.com.au/2014/08/timeshifted-su