uitarstorage.com/bee-3-philly-vintage-guitar-convention-review/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120718225258/http://www.guitarstorage.com/bee-3-philly-vintage-guitar-convention-review/ |archive-date=2012-07-18 |url-status=dead |title=Bee 3 Philly Vintage Guitar Convention Review &#124; GuitarStorage.com |accessdate=2015-09-06 }}</ref> subsequently (2013) auctioned at Heritage Auctions, Dallas, details here,<ref name=\"ha\">{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.ha.com/itm/musical-instruments/acoustic-guitars/1941-martin-d-45-natural-acoustic-guitar-serial-78882/a/7077-46008.s|title=itm/musical-instruments/acoustic-guitars/1941-martin-d-45-natural-acoustic-guitar-serial-78882/a/7077-46008|publisher=entertainment.ha.com|accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref> fairly heavily restored though with partially original finish (sold price $110,500). The same instrument was subsequently offered for sale by Carter Vintage Guitars in January 2016, inventory no. GF959, asking price $150,000.<ref name=\"carter2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cartervintage.com/acguitar/martins/martinguitars.html#d451941|title=Carter Vintage Guitars: Martin D-45, 1941|publisher=Carter Vintage Guitars|accessdate=2016-02-03}}</ref>\n|-\n| 78883 || 1941|| [E] || Surfaced in 2018, offered for sale by Gryphon Stringed Instruments, California, asking price $135,000 in May 2018;<ref name=\"gryphon2018\">{{cite web|url=https://shop.gryphonstrings.com/products/1941-steel-string-acoustic-martin-guitar-d45-53459|title=1941 Martin Guitar D-45|publisher=gryphonstrings.com|accessdate=2018-05-07}}</ref> refinished; since sold (June 2018).\n|-\n| 78884 || 1941\n|-\n| 79583 || 1941 || [E] || Surfaced in 2011, auctioned at Skinner's, Boston<ref name=\"skinnerinc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.skinnerinc.com/auctions/2569B/lots/18|title=American Guitar, C.F. Martin & Company, Nazareth, 1941, Style D-45 &#124; Sale Number 2569B, Lot Number 18 &#124; Skinner Auctioneers|publisher=skinnerinc.com|accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref