rument illustrated with a sold price $165,000 on this web page about the 2012 Dallas International Guitar Festival.<ref name=\"huffingtonpost\">{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/billrobinson/backstage-pass-the-dallas_b_1556031.html|title=BACKSTAGE PASS: The Dallas International Guitar Festival ... My Search for the World's Most Valuable Guitar&nbsp;&#124;&nbsp;Bill_Robinson|publisher=huffingtonpost.com|accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref>\n|-\n| 75102 || 1940 || [E]<ref name=\"martind45masterlist2\"/> ||\n|-\n| 75103 || 1940\n|-\n| 75104 || 1940 || [E] || Known to exist, repaired by Martin during the period 1966-2001 according to this blog post;<ref name=\"martind45-repairs-1966-2001\" /> currently in Japan in the collection of the well known popular singer [[Fukuyama Masaharu]].<ref name=\"martind45howmanyp5\"/>\n|-\n| 75105 || 1940 || [E] || Known to exist, cited in a post by John Arnold in this web page,<ref name=\"martind45howmanyp4\"/> seen at Gruhn Guitars. Refinished.\n|-\n| 75289 || 1940 || [E] || D-45L (Left hand). In the same family since the 1940s, in the United States.<ref name=\"leftyfrets\">{{cite web|url=http://www.leftyfrets.net/showthread.php?8392-1940-d45L&p=101193|title=1940 d45L - LeftyFrets.net|publisher=leftyfrets.net|accessdate=2016-05-03}}</ref> Original finish.  \n|-\n| 75593 || 1940\n|-\n| 75594 || 1940 || [E] || In the collection of Mac Yasuda, illustrated on the front cover of the \"Martin Guitar Book\", see reference below\n|-\n| 75595 || 1940 || [E] || Nicknamed \"Old Red\", formerly owned by Grant Boatright, see here.<ref name=\"facebook2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/MartinD45/photos/a.404929629526018.101467.403591896326458/889141167771526/?type=1|title=Martin D-45 - Timeline Photos &#124; Facebook|publisher=facebook.com|accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref> This guitar is presently in the collection of [[Jonathan Kellerman]],<ref name=\"martind45masterlist\"/> and is included (among other guitars from his collection) in an article in \"Vintage Guitar\", October 2005.<ref name=\"vintageguitar\">{{cite web|url=http://www.vintageguitar.com/17888/collection-of-jonathan-kellerman/|title=Collection of Jonathan Kellerman &#124;|publisher=vintageguitar.com|accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref>\n|-\n| 75596 || 1940 || [E] || Illustrated on a Japanese website here,<ref name=\"tcgakki\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tcgakki.com/fair/71c.html#st|title=THE\u4e2d\u53e4\u697d\u5668\u5c4b/\u697d\u5668\u8cb7\u53d6\u308a\u3068\u8ca9\u58f2\uff5c\u81f3\u9ad8\u306e\u9038\u54c1\u3001\u30d7\u30ea\u30a6\u30a9\u30fc\u30fb\u30de\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3\u30f3\u304c\u5947\u8de1\u306e\u5927\u96c6\u7d50!!|publisher=tcgakki.com|accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref> also on pp.&nbsp;27\u201328 of the (Japanese) \"Martin Vintage Guitar Guide\",<ref name=\"amazon.com\"/> pages also reproduced here.<ref name=\"martind45howmanyp4\"/> Currently in the collection of Nakakita Hideki, where it has been nicknamed [[Asano Yoshinaga]] after a 16th Century Japanese samurai warrior.<ref name=\"martind45howmanyp5\"/>\n|-\n| 75597 || 1940\n|-\n| 75598 || 1940 || [E] || Known to exist, cited in a post by John Arnold in this web page,<ref name=\"martind45howmanyp4\"/> having been repaired in his workshop\n|-\n| 77060 || 1941\n|-\n| 77061 || 1941\n|-\n| 77062 || 1941\n|-\n| 77063 || 1941 || [E] || Purchased new in 1941, currently in the possession of the original owner's daughter, see this post on the UMGF guitar forum.<ref name=\"UMGF1941-d-45-s-n-77063\">{{cite web|url=https://umgf.com/1941-d-45-s-n-77063-recently-accounted-for-t200588.html|title=1941 D-45 , S/N 77063 , recently accounted for !|author=|work=The Unofficial Martin Guitar Forum}}</ref>\n|-\n| 77064 || 1941 || [E] || Featured in \"The History of the American Guitar\" by Tony Bacon (UK edition), see here<ref name=\"google3\">{{cite book|title=History of the American Guitar: 1833 to the Present Day|author=Bacon, T.|date=2012|publisher=Backbeat Books|isbn=9781476856377|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=41hMAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT154#v=onepage|accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref>\n|-\n| 77065 || 1941 || [E] || Previously sold by Elderly Instruments here (archived page from 2004, last advertised price $110,000 (previously $140,000)).<ref name=\"elderly\">{{cite web|url=http://www.elderly.com/vintage/items/10U-2938.htm|title=MARTIN D-45 (1941) (10U-2938) - Elderly Instruments|publisher=elderly.com|accessdate=2015-09-06|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923235014/http://www.elderly.com/vintage/items/10U-2938.htm|archivedate=2015-09-23}}</ref> Apparently now in Japan, illustrated on pp.&nbsp;29\u201330 of the (Japanese) \"Martin Vintage Guitar Guide\",<ref name=\"amazon.com\"/> pages also reproduced here,<ref name=\"martind45howmanyp4\"/> with incorrect serial number (\"77066\")\n|-\n| 78629 || 1941 || [E] || Surfaced in 2015, for sale at Norman's Rare Guitars according to information in this thread,<ref name=\"yuku7\">{{cite web|url=http://theunofficialmartinguitarforum.yuku.com/topic/170541/Norm-got-a-41-D45?page=1|title=Norm got a '41 D-45 in The Vintage Corner Forum|publisher=theunofficialmartinguitarforum.yuku.com|accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref> asking price $285,000 (later $250,000 as at November 2015). 2 YouTube videos available here;<ref name=\"youtube\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KSqd_yYvc4U|title=Rare Martin 1941 D-45 here at Norman&#39;s Rare Guitars - YouTube|publisher=youtube.com|accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref><ref name=\"youtube2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VP2Tdgub4_0|title=Rare Martin 1941 D-45 Part 2 at Norman&#39;s Rare Guitars - YouTube |publisher=youtube.com |accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref> subsequently appears in the collection of the Songbirds Guitar Museum in Chattanooga, Tennessee, refer this \"exhibits\" page<ref name=\"songbirdsguitars\">{{cite web|url=https://songbirdsguitars.com/museum-exhibits/|title=The Songbirds Guitar Collection|publisher=songbirdsguitars.com|accessdate=2017-03-04}}</r