uary 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.twangcentral.com.au/products/1942-martin-d45|title=Twangcentral Guitars ? 1941 Martin D45 #78634|work=twangcentral.com.au}}</ref>\n|-\n| 78879 || 1941 || [E] || Originally surfaced on e-Bay in 2008, see here,<ref name=\"turbolift\">{{cite web|url=http://mysql.turbolift.com/cgi-bin/martindb.cgi/Serial?Serial=78879|title=Serial #78879|publisher=mysql.turbolift.com|accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref> also again since then for $250,000 (in January 2009).<ref name=\"martind45masterlist\"/> \n|-\n| 78880 || 1941 || &nbsp; || Appraised by Gruhn in 1973 for then owner [[Ben Speer]] of the [[Speer Family]] gospel group;<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=820011738725&set=a.518218100595&type=3&theater Copy of appraisal note on Facebook]</ref> present whereabouts/continued existence not publicly known.\n|-\n| 78881 || 1941 || [E] || Known to exist, repaired by Martin during the period 1966-2001 according to this blog post.<ref name=\"martind45-repairs-1966-2001\" />\n|-\n| 78882 || 1941 || [E] || Surfaced in 2012 at the Philadelphia Vintage Guitar Convention,<ref name=\"guitarstorage\">{{cite web|url=https://www.guitarstorage.com/bee-3-philly-vintage-guitar-convention-review/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120718225258/http://www.guitarstorage.com/bee-3-philly-vintage-guitar-convention-review/ |archive-date=2012-07-18 |url-status=dead |title=Bee 3 Philly Vintage Guitar Convention Review &#124; GuitarStorage.com |accessdate=2015-09-06 }}</ref> subsequently (2013) auctioned at Heritage Auctions, Dallas, details here,<ref name=\"ha\">{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.ha.com/itm/musical-instruments/acoustic-guitars/1941-martin-d-45-natural-acoustic-guitar-serial-78882/a/7077-46008.s|title=itm/musical-instruments/acoustic-guitars/1941-martin-d-45-natural-acoustic-guitar-serial-78882/a/7077-46008|publisher=entertainment.ha.com|accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref> fairly heavily restored though with partially original finish (sold price $110,500). The same instrument was subsequently offered for sale by Carter Vintage Guitars in January 2016, inventory no. GF959, asking price $150,000.<ref name=\"carter2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cartervintage.com/acguitar/martins/martinguitars.html#d451941|title=Carter Vintage Guitars: Martin D-45, 1941|publisher=Carter Vintage Guitars|accessdate=2016-02-03}}</ref>\n|-\n| 78883 || 1941|| [E] || Surfaced in 2018, offered for sale by Gryphon Stringed Instruments, California, asking price $135,000 in May 2018;<ref name=\"gryphon2018\">{{cite web|url=https://shop.gryphonstrings.com/products/1941-steel-string-acoustic-martin-guitar-d45-53459|title=1941 Martin Guitar D-45|publisher=gryphonstrings.com|accessdate=2018-05-07}}</ref> refinished; since sold (June 2018).\n|-\n| 78884 || 1941\n|-\n| 79583 || 1941 || [E] || Surfaced in 2011, auctioned at Skinner's, Boston<ref name=\"skinnerinc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.skinnerinc.com/auctions/2569B/lots/18|title=American Guitar, C.F. Martin & Company, Nazareth, 1941, Style D-45 &#124; Sale Number 2569B, Lot Number 18 &#124; Skinner Auctioneers|publisher=skinnerinc.com|accessdate=2015-09-06}}</ref> (sold price $219,225), subsequently on sale at Rumbleseat Music, CA, and at Carter Vintage Guitars; some additional photos here<ref name=\"fretboardjournal\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fretboardjournal.com/blog/catch-day-1941-martin-d-45|title=Catch of the Day: 1941 Martin D-45 &#124; The Fretboard Journal: Keepsake magazine for guitar collectors|publisher=fretboardjournal.com|accessdate=2015-09-06|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150918185600/http://www.fretboardjournal.com/blog/catch-day-1941-martin-d-45|archivedate=2015-09-18}}</ref> and here,<ref name=\"yuku8\">{{cite web|url=http://theunofficialmartinguitarforum.yuku.com/topic/149658/Played-a-1942-D45-and-1940-D28-Today|title=Played a 1942 D-45 and 1940 D-28 Today... in The Vintage Corner Forum|publisher=theunofficialmartinguitarforum.yuku.com|a